  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">RVO IMVO Pension Conv. VCP</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The Pension Convenant seeks to support Pension Funds to implement OECD orientations regarding ESG.
The two track approach has a general track where all Dutch pension funds are targetted and a second track to undertake case studies and feed into the general track.

The Convenant will work with a Steering Group and several working groups, notably for Monitoring, Case Studies and Instruments.

The Convenant support facility is not a project but a facility where Oxfam Novib, on behalf of participating NGOs and trade unions, administers the facility. On an equal basis, Oxfam Novib also participates in the implementation of the Convenant.

Trade unions in particular share knowledge and information about labor rights, including freedom of association, collective bargaining and living wage, in the local context in which abuses can occur. They thereby make an important contribution to the efforts of Participating Pension Funds to prevent, detect, mitigate and remedy potential abuses in the field of labor rights.
The trade unions involved will collect and share the knowledge and information of their worldwide partner organizations and of international departments with the other Parties. They will also coordinate activities where possible. With regard to the Deep Track, they will play an active role wherever possible in involving local stakeholders, (informally) mediating sensitive or complex issues and / or conducting public-oriented activities or other activities aimed at increasing joint influence. on companies.</narrative>
  </description>
